<?xml version='1.0'?>
<!-- The following defines colours and objects/fields for colour by as 
follows. See the contents of this file for examples.

Colour groups are defined as <colour_map name=""> entries each of which has a colour
value that may be of the form "RRGGBB" or a name as defined by colour.called().
The colour_map name is optional and defaults to "default". 

Object/field/value/colour mappings are defined as follows:

    <field_type dataset="" name="" colour_map="">
	<object name="" field_name=""/>
    <field_type>

    Defines top level entries as shown in the application and each entry 
    is keyed on <dataset>_<name>. External strings must be defined in the 
    eo_colour_by message group using this convention. E.g :electric_eo_line_voltage

    dataset: The dataset name such as "electric"

    name: The field type name such as "eo_line_voltage" which must be enumerated or 
    which must be a field name included in the list of non_enum_fields of colour by config 
    and suitable code added to colour by config to generate the lists of values and colours 
    needed, for example the colour by circuit.

    domain: This is an optional entry, if included it must be the name of a domain of the 
    field type entered in name.  This will limit the list of available values to those of
    the domain.  Any value of the field type that is not included in the dmoain can be mapped 
    to a value in the domain using a domain_value entry.  

    colour_map: The optional name of a colour map which defaults to "default". Note
    that colours are assigned to enum values in the order given.

    This contains zero or more <object>s as defined below. If no objects
    are specified, the entire dataset is searched for objects with fields 
    of the specified type.

<object>
    One or more objects and related fields.

    name: The collection name in the dataset which must exist
    field_name: If defined it must be the correct parent field_type and be
    enumerated. If omitted the first field with that type is used.

<domain_value>
    for field type entries using a domain to restrict the list of values the dmoain_value entry 
    is used to map additional values to the domain values.  For example the eo_phase field type
    contains all values for phasing such as A, AB, BA, ABC, BAC...  The eo_phasing domain is 
    restricted to the values A, AB, ABC... The domain_value entry maps the value BA to AB, so 
    in hte colour by dialog only AB is listed but all objects with the values AB or BA will be 
    drawn in the same colour.  value must be in the domain and additional value must be in the 
    field type but not in the domain.
    
Performance: This is not intended to be used with large numbers of 
objects/enum_values. It is recommended that small numbers are used for
this otherwise rendering performance will be affected.
-->

